The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 August is 62,655 (7,221.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 August, there were 2,548 new confirmed cases (293.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 August, there were 2,436 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% (112 extra cases).
